wikipedia_page.main: Ashby Blair Haslewood (1810 – 17 July 1876) was an English clergyman and educationalist who as a young man played first-class cricket for Cambridge University. Haslewood was born in 1810 in Wimbledon, then considered part of Surrey, but the exact date of birth is not known; he was christened at Hampstead on 16 July 1811 and he died in 1876 at Marylebone.
